Raspadskaya Falls Most in Week on Koksovaya Mine Accident

-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n
-- 
2011-04-05T15:39:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/raspadskaya-falls-most-in-week-on-koksovaya-mine-accident-1-.html
OAO  Raspadskaya (RASP)  fell the most in a
week after the Russian producer of coal for steelmaking halted
operations at its Koksovaya mine in Siberia following an
accident yesterday.  The shares slid as much as 2.5 percent and fell 1.6 percent
to 185.92 rubles by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, the steepest
drop since March 29.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alexander Nicholson at 
 anicholson6@bloomberg.net  